observations.recommendation:
We recommended and Management, through the Municipal Accountant, agreed to:
Prepare separate subsidiary ledgers for each road component and LRN Ledger Cards for each local road;
Present in the Notes to Financial Statements the required disclosures pertaining to the road network system;
We also recommended and Management, through the Municipal Treasurer agreed to:
In coordination with the other members of the Inventory Committee, prepare and maintain a Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System and the Road Map;
Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components; and
We further recommended and Management, through the Municipal Engineer, agreed to:
Provide assistance to the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer in determining the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

We recommended and Management, through the BAC Chairperson, agreed to:
Submit justification for the above-mentioned deficiencies/non-adherence to RA No. 9184;
Submit certification from the BAC Secretariat that the Invitation to Bid was posted at any conspicuous place reserved for its purpose in the premises of the Procuring Entity concerned for seven calendar days;
Submit BAC and SB resolutions signed by the concurring members;
Comply with the provisions/guidelines on the invitation of observers during the bidding process and on the posting of Notice of Award and Notice to Proceed in the PhilGEPs;
Scrutinize carefully the submitted legal, technical and financial documents of bidders; and
Account for those materials used in the fabrication of Christmas lights and decorations which may be reutilized by the Agency in their prospective events or activities.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require:
a.	Driver/s assigned to motor vehicle present a duly accomplished and approved Trip Ticket/s to support the requisition for fuel issuance;
b.	Designated personnel to prepare the Monthly Reports of Fuel Consumption and Official Travels with all the necessary information and make available to the auditor for verification purposes.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor require:
Driver/s assigned to motor vehicle present a duly accomplished and approved Trip Ticket/s to support the requisition for fuel issuance;
Designated personnel to prepare the Monthly Reports of Fuel Consumption and Official Travels with all the necessary information and make available to the auditor for verification purposes.

We recommended that the Municipal Accountant ensure that the acquired assets and liabilities of BWD are carried in the books of the LGU:
Secure a copy of the detailed assets and liabilities of the BWD immediately after the dissolution and acceptance by the LGU;
Record the acquired assets and liabilities under special accounts in the general fund as required under Section 313 of RA 7160;
Provide sufficient disclosures in the financial statements regarding the financial accounts of the BWD which were not yet audited; and,
Provide a copy of the JEV to the auditor

